ginni rometty  wikipedia ginni rometty from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search ginni rometty rometty at the  fortune most powerful women summit born virginia marie nicosia  july   age  chicago illinois united states nationality american education northwestern university bs occupation chairman president and ceo of ibm salary us million  predecessor samuel j palmisano virginia marie ginni rometty born july   is an american business executive she is the current chairman president and ceo of ibm and the first woman to head the company prior to becoming president and ceo in january  she held the positions of senior vice president and group executive for sales marketing and strategy at ibm she joined ibm as a systems engineer in its detroit office in  romettys tenure as ceo has been marked by prestigious awards including by bloomberg who named her among the  most influential people in the world and fortune naming her among the  most powerful women in business for ten consecutive years her tenure as ceo has been met by criticism related to executive compensation and outsourcing and ibms  consecutive quarters of revenue decline contents  early life and education  career  boards and honors  criticism  personal life  references  external links early life and educationedit rometty graduated from the robert r mccormick school of engineering and applied science at northwestern university in  with high honors receiving a bachelors degree in computer science and electrical engineering rometty was a member of the kappa kappa gamma sorority eventually serving as its president careeredit after graduation in  rometty went to work for general motors institute in  she joined ibm as a systems engineer in its detroit office she joined ibms consulting group in  in  she championed the purchase of the big business consulting firm pricewaterhousecoopers consulting for  billion rometty became senior vice president and group executive for sales marketing and strategy in  and is credited with spearheading ibms growth strategy by getting the company into the cloud computing and analytics businesses she was also at the helm of readying watson the jeopardy playing computer for commercial use on october   ibm announced that she was to be the companys next president and ceo with sam palmisano stepping down but retaining his position as chairman romettys appointment marks the first time a woman has been ceo of ibm regarding her promotion palmisano stated ginni got it because she deserved it it’s got zero to do with progressive social policies on september   ibm announced that rometty was taking on the added role of chairman of ibm as samuel palmisano prepared to retire at the end of  rometty commenced her duty as chairman president and ceo of ibm on october   one of her goals is to focus company efforts on the cloud and cognitive computing systems such as watson on march   rometty who is a part of a white house businessadvisory council under the trump administration was included in a business leaders symposium during german chancellor angela merkels visit to washington boards and honorsedit rometty serves on the council on foreign relations the board of trustees of her alma mater northwestern university the board of overseers and board of managers of memorial sloankettering cancer center and is a council member at the latin america conservation council a subsidiary of the nature conservancy she also served on the board of directors of aig from  until  in  rometty was featured in the pbs documentary the boomer list also that year she became the third female member of the augusta national golf club she has received honorary doctoral degrees from rensselaer polytechnic institute  and northwestern university  in fortunes september   issue rometty ranked rd on their most powerful women list named the th most powerful woman on the  forbes list the worlds  most powerful women criticismedit over romettys tenure as ceo she has been met by increasing criticism most notably a confrontation with mark cuban who said she had lacked vision with ibm losing revenue now for  consecutive quarters in a row ibm employees have also criticized her for taking pay bonuses despite massive layoffs of ibm employees and poor performance rometty has been named among the worst ceos by several publications including the motley fool  wallstreet forbes and the wall street journal  personal lifeedit rometty is married to mark anthony rometty a principal investor in the bam oil company the couple has no children referencesedit  virginia rometty prezicom retrieved  july    waters richard more than a big smile on big blue’s face october   financial times retrieved  july    httpwwwbusinessinsidercomibmpaidromettymillioninirt  aluise susan j may   america’s  most powerful female ceos investorplace retrieved  july    barnett megan november   buffett goes big in big blue fortune retrieved  july    a b ibm names rometty to succeed palmisano as first female ceo bloomberg businessweek  october  retrieved  october  permanent dead link  a b ibm’s ginni rometty completes her ascent by adding chairman role bloomberg retrieved  september    forbes magazines worlds  most powerful people in the worlds  most powerful forbes   time  in mayer marissa  april  the  most influential people in the world time retrieved  april     most influential list of bloomberg markets magazine in september   ginni rometty fortune  september  retrieved  september    ginni rometty fortune   ceos who have to go  wall street   fortune magazine gets a raise despite tumbling stock price   mark cuban slams ibm its no longer a tech company they have no vision business insider retrieved    nu appoints  new members to board of trustees northwestern university june   archived from the original on june   retrieved    hempel jessi  october  ibms ginni rometty looks ahead fortune   a b c ibm names virginia rometty as first female ceo wired october   retrieved    a b ibm names virginia 